Absolutely amazing masterpiece with the masterminds of balancing developers of valve. This games community, game play, and progression is unremarkable. The community is friendly and accepting with friendlies from the opposite team dancing and enjoying the stay. With the game play having various different approaches for your liking with 9 different classes with also sub classes in those classes as unlock-able weapons such as troll soldier or demo-knight. As well the progression having extensive work and always giving the player something new to try and figure out what works best for their liking. This game in summary is amazing with amazing game play with amazing well developed maps and balancing between classes. One hundred percent would recommend to anyone and all.

The game has so much potential and offers an incredible experienceâ€”when you actually get to play it. Unfortunately, the matchmaking system seems to have been designed with the noble goal of testing the limits of your patience and the expansiveness of your free time. If you enjoy waiting around and savoring the inefficiency of a system that seems more focused on wasting your time than matching you with players, then this is the game for you. For anyone else, Iâ€™d recommend thinking carefully about how much patience and spare time you truly have before diving in.

TF2 is a timeless classic. My time in this game from 2009 to 2012 was awesome.

Stopped playing when the games roadmap changed from fun team shooter with a competitive base to a hat collecting simulator and then unbalanced weapon generator. I believe when the Liberty launcher released is when I finally uninstalled (this was after dealing with the FaN on scout for half a year)

Some of the worst updates to ever touch the game. I am sure there's been dozens of updates since then but I could never enjoy it the same. Just hundreds of hours perfecting classes to have easier ones release undermining them.

Anyway sure the game is still tons of fun to play for the new generation. I'm surprised a team fortress 3 on source 2 hasn't come yet. Also I would pay money to go back to the version I used to play in 2010.
